'.\" -*- nroff -*-
.TH MOUNT.KAFS 8 "2026-03-21" "kafs 0.4.0" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
mount.kafs \- mount helper for KAFS FUSE images
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mount.kafs
.I image
.I mountpoint
.RI [ FUSE\ options ]
.PP
.B mount
.B -t
.B fuse.kafs
.I image
.I mountpoint
.RI [ -o\ opt[,opt...] ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B mount.kafs
is a thin compatibility wrapper around
.BR kafs (1).
It exists so that KAFS can be mounted through the conventional
.BR mount (8)
helper path while the filesystem implementation remains in userspace via FUSE.
.PP
The helper forwards all arguments to
.BR kafs .
When invoked from
.BR mount " -t " fuse.kafs ,
the image path is passed as the first non-option argument and is accepted by the existing
.B kafs
mount helper compatibility parser.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Direct helper invocation
.nf
mount.kafs /var/lib/kafs/data.img /mnt/kafs -o allow_other,multi_thread=8
.fi
.SS Via mount(8)
.nf
mount -t fuse.kafs /var/lib/kafs/data.img /mnt/kafs -o allow_other,multi_thread=8
.fi
.SS /etc/fstab
.nf
/var/lib/kafs/data.img  /mnt/kafs  fuse.kafs  rw,nofail,allow_other,multi_thread=8  0  0
.fi
.PP
The first field is the KAFS image file and the third field remains
.B fuse.kafs
because the kernel-visible filesystem type is FUSE, not a native in-kernel KAFS registration.
.SH NOTES
.TP
.B /proc/filesystems
will not list
.B kafs
as a standalone native filesystem type while KAFS is implemented via FUSE.
.TP
.B mount options
accepted here are the same options documented for
.BR kafs (1),
including KAFS-specific
.BR -o " " multi_thread= ,
.BR hotplug ,
and related tuning knobs.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR kafs (1),
.BR mount (8),
.BR fstab (5),
.BR fusermount3 (1)
.SH AUTHOR
kafs project.